##"What do you work for? " | See the female workers in the epidemic

Micro-signal Jianjiaobuluo

Function description, pepper tribe, amplify your voice! Chinese Women Workers Exclusive Information Platform, you are welcome to pay attention!

ABSRTACT: There are hundreds of reasons behind "I am not afraid" .

The new coronary pneumonia's shadow has not yet dispersed, many areas already successively resumed the work. People are trying to rebuild their jobs and lives, and some of them have never left their jobs.

What challenges do workers face and how do they respond to the epidemic? What are their biggest worries and concerns? We focus on the faces and voices of women workers in different industries.

Aunt Ho, the sanitation worker
"It's no big deal. "

Aunt he didn't come home for the New Year, not because of the epidemic, but because of work. She has five days of annual leave per year, but the company always urges its employees to take it early, and when the new year comes, they are not allowed to take it. The He Yi to this understanding is, "had retired nobody to sweep the road, nobody to engage in the hygiene" .
The outbreak has made her job a little easier, with only one day off a week. Now employees can take two days off a week for safety reasons. Beyond that, the impact on her life was limited. The sanitation worker has a heavy workload, leaving the house before dawn at 5:30 a.m. , and keeping her area clean during her shift means walking around almost nonstop. She said she was too busy to even read the news, and did not know how severe the outbreak was or how many cases there had been.
Now every day at work, the Monitor will come to hair mask, temperature, temperature records to report to the company. These routines didn't make her more worried about her situation -- she was out working for money, afraid that she would have to work all the time, working every day as exercise. Because still can go to work, the family's economic situation also has not been affected, "quite good" .
In between jobs, she talked about her daughter, who was in college in her hometown, and wondered how she was doing in school and her grades. College is expensive. It's a lot of money.

Xiao-hong, delivery boy
"No matter how well protected, you can catch it. "

Xiaohong and her colleagues are deeply impressed by the impact the epidemic has had on people's lives as "riders" of food delivery.
Xiaohong recalls, years ago, there are many people online to buy masks, she kept sending masks every day, still feel very strange in the heart. At the time, the company did not realize the seriousness of the situation, "did not expect to have such a frightening disease, " the rider himself did not wear a mask, as usual home delivery. By the time she realized she was buying masks, they were all sold out. On the first day of the New Year, the company held an emergency meeting, which equipped everyone with face masks and disinfectant.
By the second day, Xiaohong began to feel afraid. She went to the supermarket to pick up the goods and was met with a panic buying of grain. Originally during the New Year, the workload should be small, but those days of looting her tired enough. Soon, the community and Urban village began to restrict access, and her main job changed from food delivery to food delivery.
At the beginning of the village to show identity cards, all of Hubei are not allowed to enter. Xiaohong for Hubei Colleagues to complain: Many people have not been home for several years, but also by "one shot killed. ". There are also village rules that "people can enter, but cars can't" . Xiao Hong thought it was funny: "people spread the virus, not cars. " The village was very big, and she walked on two legs for a few days, and the rules for closing the village came down again, take-out can only deliver to the village from now on, wait for the customer to come out to pick up.
In their haste, the delivery men sometimes joked together. Some said they were still afraid of dying. Others had a bottle of disinfectant in their car. He had two. On the other hand, they are also the least afraid of death. Xiao Hong worried about the return of worry, but there is a heart almost "destiny" of open-minded, "every day in the outside run, and how to protect well, to infect the" . She asked her family not to visit her in Guangzhou, but she did not want to go back home, after all, to quarantine, it is better to stay and work. Her relatives envied her. They didn't go to work for a month or two, and she had at least an income.

Liu Jie, a vegetable vendor
"There's definitely going to be some impact. "

The vegetable market, which had been open since the eighth day of the previous year, has only started to recover this year. Liu Jie returned to Guangzhou from home, at home, "self-isolation" for half a month, now settled online class children, their own out to do business.
In terms of material reserves, Liu Jie's family is relatively "lucky. ". We have land, fish ponds, and chickens. Even if we can't buy food during the epidemic, we don't have to worry about food rations for the new year. When she saw her friends'circle on the eve of her 30th year, she learned that the supermarkets in Guangzhou had been snapped up. Alcohol and disinfectants are also available at home, the only trouble is that the mask, pharmacies are sold out, and finally had to ask someone else, only got 10. AT $5 a pop, it doesn't look too high these days.
Back in the city, sister Liu found life at home a little boring. Can't do business, can't go out to play cards, can't get together for dinner, can only watch TV at home all day, sleep. The state of the economy is also affected to some extent, can not earn money, but spend money in the same place. "You have to eat at home, you have to pay rent, right? " The epidemic is not over yet, but people have to live, to eat, to buy food. Sister Liu's shop has opened again.

Wu Yi community volunteer
"there must be pressure. "

Wu, a native of Guangzhou, has been working as a landlord in her home town of Urban village since Feb. 5, registering residents at the entrance to the village and dealing with the comings and goings in her less-than-fluent Mandarin. As for the volunteer work, she said simply: "It's not up to you to be afraid. So many out-of-towners come back, come on duty. "
According to Wu, during the epidemic, people were unable to find jobs outside and their homes were not allowed to be rented out. Even local people faced financial pressure.

Ali clothing sales
"Do you really want to go to work because you've been home so long? "

In the middle of the shoot, Ali suddenly said, "let me sterilize you. " She took out the alcohol and sprayed the photographer.
Like many young people who live alone, she spent a period of time eating instant noodles at home in her pajamas before returning to work. Ali was glad that she had bought two more sets of pajamas before the New Year, and they were immediately put to use. Some people around had a large number of masks packed early. Ali, who was full of tension about the spread of the epidemic, had not packed them, because think this is a kind of"very ashamed behavior":"You store me, everybody can not buy, what about those who have no use?"She only bought enough for herself.
On the day of the shoot, only one guest showed up, and the atmosphere was relaxed. She honestly said that she didn't want to go to work at all. After lying at home for a month, she just wanted to go for a walk and relax. She also had to be able to afford to go to Harvard. Of all the effects of the epidemic, "No money" was the most important.

Aunt Lee, the doorman
"As you can see, I haven't had a day off. "

Aunt Li didn't come home for the New Year, just like any other year. She works all the year round and gets docked if she takes a day off. In fact, the original monthly should have 4 days off, but the doorman monthly salary is only 2100, if the rest day overtime, a day can make up 70 yuan, in order to this monthly 280 yuan, aunt Li tried to insist on no rest.

She and her husband were both doormen, and at night he would take her place. Two people's meager wages, to support the health of a son and a daughter. My daughter is still in her senior year of high school this year. Not only does she have to pay tuition, but she also needs more than 1,000 yuan a week for medicine. The doctor said the medicine needs to eat 3 months in a row, aunt Li hopes this 3 months can let the daughter Heal:"(disease) can cut the root on the good, no cut the root (later) can't afford AH."
The family's money is used to fill the hole, there is no savings, and now aunt Li and her husband live in a very small single room, a month rent 700. She had only lived two months, and with the deposit she had paid more than two thousand, plus the cost of sanitation, water and electricity, as well as the expenses of daily life and her hometown
My daughter is staying here, too. Aunt Li did not buy a smartphone, not on the Internet, "virus"-related information is the daughter told her. The unit did not give the staff masks, let them buy their own, said that when the epidemic past reimbursement, but also thanks to the daughter early bought ready at home. At first Li Yi did not feel the situation is serious, said to wear a mask uncomfortable, do not want to wear, her daughter let her endure, must wear: "Life is the most important! "

A lucky medical worker
"I'm not afraid. "

A Xing is in charge of infectious disease prevention and control in a community health service center. After the epidemic spread, the community center's medical staff actively participated in the epidemic prevention and control work, leaving early and returning late, sometimes arranged 24-hour duty, or even more than 30 hours of overwork. A Xing is one of them, to a home every day, Hubei residents back to do health follow-up.
There is a shortage of medical staff at the grass-roots level, and there is a shortage of protective materials. As the first-line prevention and control personnel, their life safety can not be guaranteed. However, everyone believes that they have an obligation to contribute in the face of disasters, which can also be said to be a hindrance to their profession itself, there are few complaints that it is their duty to protect the health of their inhabitants.
She said she had "become desensitized" to the concept of time. After six days of follow-up work, she began to experience muscle soreness, chest tightness, headache and other symptoms due to fatigue caused by the intensity of work. She was worried that she would become "asymptomatic" and infect others at work. She set herself up for tests, and while waiting for the results, she slept for two days -- as if her body were on alert, reminding her that she needed to rest.
But lucky said not tired, but also want to participate in community volunteer service, continue to work. The results of the physical exam came back, and there was no infection. She immediately returned to her post.
Stand in the front line of the fight against the epidemic, every day to contact a large number of people, while constantly hearing news reports of medical staff infection, whether there is a wavering heart and fear? Ah Hsing said she was not afraid, years of work experience let her know, for her, the most important thing is how to calm the panic of residents, more quickly to start work.
"I'm not afraid. This outbreak has already claimed the lives of many people, including our medical staff, and I am afraid that if we do not take action to contain it, the next person whose life is at stake may be the most important person around us."

Aunt Huang, the cleaner
"I wouldn't do this job if I knew I was going to die. "

Huang did not wear a mask when she first learned of the outbreak. The residents of the neighborhood saw, someone asked: "Aunt you do not wear a mask ah? " Huang Aunt said nothing, he is not afraid to die, "know that the words do not do this work. ".
But as the situation grew worse, she finally put it on. The face mask property isn't in Florida, so in addition to the $5,000 a month that Huang and her husband are "contracted" to do the cleaning, the face masks and gloves are labor protection items, including garbage bags, disinfectant and dishwashing liquid, they basically have to buy it themselves. The mask that Huang aunt uses is before others move to throw away, she"picked up"came out, a bag is still new, had come in handy now. At first she was reluctant to use it, wearing a mask for two or three days. Now there are twenty left in the house.
Special period, cleaning garbage in the eyes of others may be very dangerous, but the mentality of Huang Yi has not changed. Her carefulness is obvious to all, the neighborhood committee to check, all praised her clean. Huang aunt thinks this is a matter of course: "since want to do, want to clean up, disrelish dirty certainly did not do. "

Additional: photographer's notes
The shoot and the interview were done in the form of street interviews, with great nervousness that every hard won opportunity would be suddenly interrupted, every time Split Second. Have been rejected many times, but still want to seize every possible, try again.
One of the most moving words I heard in the process was, "the application was not approved, but thank you for speaking up for us women. " I felt it was worth it. I'd like to thank everyone who's willing to be interviewed and filmed.
